Comment (src/views/control-implementations/partials/ControlStatementSuggestions.vue:15):
**Low: functions passed as props bypass Vue reactivity**

`isSuggestionApplied`, `isSuggestionApplying`, and `formatRelevanceScore` are passed in as callable props. Vue doesn't track when these closures capture stale state, so a reactive change in the parent that affects these functions won't automatically re-render this component unless the functions themselves are recreated.

More idiomatic fix:
- Replace the two predicate props with derived data: `appliedUuids: Set<string>` and `applyingUuids: Set<string>` — the template can do `appliedUuids.has(suggestion.componentUuid)` directly.
- Import `formatRelevanceScore` as a standalone util inside this file so it's not in the prop contract at all.

This also makes the component easier to test in isolation (no need to pass mock functions).
