Comment (src/views/control-implementations/__tests__/IndexView.spec.ts:184):
**Low: Button stub fires click when disabled, testing the JS guard not the UI contract**

The current stub emits `click` regardless of the `disabled` prop:
```ts
'<button :disabled="disabled" ... @click="$emit(\'click\', $event)">'
```

The real PrimeVue `Button` swallows click events when `disabled`. Because of this, the test at line 253–255 (`noImplementationButton?.trigger('click')`) is actually verifying that the JS guard in `openImplementationDrawer` (`if (!req) return`) prevents the drawer from opening — not that the disabled UI state does.

To make the test accurately reflect browser behaviour, add a disabled check:
```ts
Button: {
  props: ['disabled', 'ariaLabel', 'title', 'label'],
  template: '<button :disabled="disabled" :aria-label="ariaLabel" :title="title" @click="!disabled && $emit(\'click\', $event)"><slot />{{ label }}</button>',
},
```

With this change the test would still pass (because the button *is* disabled), and you'd be testing the right thing.
